---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Code of Conduct"
  description="The ReRoll Board Games Collective Code of Conduct and community guidelines."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-4">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-sans-ui text-xs tracking-wider uppercase font-bold text-brand-red hover:text-brand-red-dark transition-colors group"
      >
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          class="h-4 w-4 transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="2.5"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path>
        </svg>
        <span>Back to Table</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div
      class="text-center mb-12 border-b border-dashed border-brand-red/20 pb-8"
    >
      <span
        class="font-sans-ui text-xs tracking-widest text-brand-red font-bold uppercase"
      >
        Community Codex & Regulations
      </span>
      <h2
        class="font-serif-title text-3xl md:text-4.5xl font-extrabold text-brand-red tracking-wide uppercase mt-2 mb-4"
      >
        Code of Conduct
      </h2>
      <p class="font-serif-body text-base italic text-text-ink-muted mt-2">
        Established for players, organizers, and guests of ReRoll events.
      </p>

      <div
        class="mt-4 inline-block bg-brand-red-pale border border-brand-red/20 py-2.5 px-5 rounded-xs"
      >
        <p
          class="font-sans-ui text-xs uppercase tracking-wider font-bold text-brand-red"
        >
          Emergency Contact: <a
            href="mailto:karthikb351@gmail.com"
            class="underline hover:text-brand-red-dark">karthikb351@gmail.com</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div
      class="prose max-w-none font-serif-body text-base md:text-lg text-text-ink leading-relaxed"
    >
      <div class="mb-10">
        <p class="rulebook-dropcap mb-4">
          We are committed to providing a friendly, safe and welcoming
          environment for all, regardless of level of expertise, gender, gender
          identity and expression, sexual orientation, disability, personal
          appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, age, religion, nationality, or
          other similar characteristic.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          This code of conduct outlines our expectations for all those who
          participate in our community, as well as the consequences for
          unacceptable behavior.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 my-8">
        <div class="h-[1px] w-full bg-brand-red/20"></div>
        <span class="text-brand-red text-xs">❖</span>
        <div class="h-[1px] w-full bg-brand-red/20"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-10">
        <h3
          class="font-serif-title text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-brand-red tracking-wide uppercase mb-4 flex items-center gap-2"
        >
          <span class="text-brand-red/60 text-sm">✦</span> Expected Behavior
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The following behaviors are expected and requested of all community
          members at our tables, online forums, and chats:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3.5 pl-6 list-none">
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Be Kind and Courteous.</strong> There's no need to be mean or
            rude. Treat new players with patience and help teach the rules when possible.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Attempt Collaboration before Conflict.</strong> Focus on having
            fun rather than winning at all costs. Friendly banter is welcome, but
            avoid hostility.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Refrain from Demeanour.</strong> Avoid demeaning, discriminatory,
            or harassing behavior and speech in all forms.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Be Mindful of Surroundings.</strong> Alert community leaders if
            you notice a dangerous situation, someone in distress, or violations of
            this Code of Conduct, even if they seem inconsequential.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Respect Event Venues.</strong> Event venues may be shared with
            members of the public; please be respectful to all patrons and staff of
            these locations.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Embrace Diversity.</strong> Respect that people have differences
            of opinion and that every individual has a different skill level, personal
            preferences, and interests.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Respect Tabletop Property.</strong> Community members are expected
            to respect the property of other members including their board games,
            tokens, cards, box art, and gaming accessories. Avoid oily food, rough
            handling, or bending cardstock.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 my-8">
        <div class="h-[1px] w-full bg-brand-red/20"></div>
        <span class="text-brand-red text-xs">❖</span>
        <div class="h-[1px] w-full bg-brand-red/20"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-10">
        <h3
          class="font-serif-title text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-brand-red tracking-wide uppercase mb-4 flex items-center gap-2"
        >
          <span class="text-brand-red/60 text-sm">✦</span> Unacceptable Behavior
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The following behaviors are considered harassment and are completely
          unacceptable within our collective:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3.5 pl-6 list-none">
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Inappropriate Nicknames.</strong> On WhatsApp, Discord, Reddit,
            Facebook, or any other online group with ReRoll, please avoid using overtly
            sexual nicknames or other nicknames that might detract from a safe, friendly,
            and welcoming environment.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Harassment & Insults.</strong> It is unacceptable to insult, demean,
            or harass anyone. We interpret the term "harassment" as including the
            definition in the <a
              href="http://citizencodeofconduct.org/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-brand-red hover:underline font-bold"
              >Citizen Code of Conduct</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Private Harassment.</strong> Private harassment is also unacceptable.
            No matter who you are, if you feel you have been or are being harassed
            or made uncomfortable by a community member, please contact one of the
            organizers immediately. Whether you're a regular member or a newcomer,
            we care about making this community a safe place for you.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Violence & Threats.</strong> Violence, threats of violence, or
            violent language directed against another person will result in immediate
            exclusion.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Offensive Commentary.</strong> Offensive comments related to gender,
            gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, disability, mental
            illness, neurotypicality, physical appearance, body size, race, age, regional
            discrimination, political or religious affiliation.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Unwelcome Lifestyle Commentary.</strong> Unwelcome comments regarding
            a person’s lifestyle choices and practices, including those related to
            food, health, parenting, drugs, and employment.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Explicit Material.</strong> Posting or displaying sexually explicit
            or violent material in any channel or physical space.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Doxing.</strong> Posting or threatening to post other people’s
            personally identifying information (“doxing”) without explicit consent.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Physical Harassment.</strong> Inappropriate physical contact.
            You must have someone’s consent before touching them and stop immediately
            after a request to stop.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Unwelcome Sexual Attention.</strong> This includes sexualized
            comments or jokes; inappropriate touching, groping, and unwelcome sexual
            advances.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span>
            <strong>Stalking & Baiting.</strong> Deliberate intimidation, stalking,
            following (online or in person), spamming, trolling, flaming, baiting,
            or other attention-stealing behavior.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 my-8">
        <div class="h-[1px] w-full bg-brand-red/20"></div>
        <span class="text-brand-red text-xs">❖</span>
        <div class="h-[1px] w-full bg-brand-red/20"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-10">
        <h3
          class="font-serif-title text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-brand-red tracking-wide uppercase mb-4 flex items-center gap-2"
        >
          <span class="text-brand-red/60 text-sm">✦</span> Consequences of Violation
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Unacceptable behavior from any community member, including sponsors
          and those with decision-making authority, will not be tolerated at any
          event or digital space.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4 italic font-bold">
          Anyone asked to stop unacceptable behavior is expected to comply
          immediately.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          If a community member engages in unacceptable behavior, the organizers
          and moderators may take action. Responses include, but are not limited
          to:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3.5 pl-6 list-none mb-4">
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span> A private
            or public warning of violating the code of conduct.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span> A formal
            request for a private or public apology.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span> A temporary
            or permanent ban from community events (without refund).
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span> A temporary
            or permanent ban from venues and online spaces.
          </li>
          <li class="relative pl-5">
            <span class="absolute left-0 text-brand-red font-bold">❖</span> Reporting
            to law enforcement or relevant authorities in serious cases.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 my-8">
        <div class="h-[1px] w-full bg-brand-red/20"></div>
        <span class="text-brand-red text-xs">❖</span>
        <div class="h-[1px] w-full bg-brand-red/20"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-10">
        <h3
          class="font-serif-title text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-brand-red tracking-wide uppercase mb-4 flex items-center gap-2"
        >
          <span class="text-brand-red/60 text-sm">✦</span> Reporting & Enforcement
          Guidelines
        </h3>
        <p class="mb-4">
          If you are subject to or witness unacceptable behavior, please notify
          a moderator or organizer as soon as possible.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          You can report inappropriate behavior to the concerned organizer (in
          case of a physical event), the admin (in case of online forums), or
          email us directly at <a
            href="mailto:karthikb351@gmail.com"
            class="text-brand-red hover:underline font-bold"
            >karthikb351@gmail.com</a
          >. All reports will be handled with strict discretion.
        </p>
        <ol class="space-y-3.5 pl-6 list-decimal mb-6">
          <li>
            Remarks that violate ReRoll's standards, including hateful or
            oppressive comments, are strictly forbidden.
          </li>
          <li>
            Remarks that moderators find inappropriate, whether listed in the
            code of conduct or not, are also not allowed.
          </li>
          <li>Moderators will first respond to infractions with a warning.</li>
          <li>
            If the warning is unheeded, the user will be temporarily removed
            ("kicked") from communication channels.
          </li>
          <li>
            If the member continues to violate guidelines, they will be
            indefinitely excluded ("banned") from all ReRoll channels, both
            online and offline.
          </li>
          <li>
            Complaints about bans in-channel are not allowed. Issues with
            warnings or bans must be discussed in private.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <p
          class="mb-4 italic bg-brand-red-pale border border-brand-red/10 p-5 rounded-xs leading-relaxed text-center"
        >
          "If someone takes issue with something you said or did, resist the
          urge to be defensive. Just stop and apologize. Even if you feel you
          were misinterpreted, remember that it's your responsibility to make
          your fellow members comfortable at the table."
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-brand-red/10 text-center">
      <p class="font-serif-body text-xs text-text-ink-muted italic">
        Adapted from the Oklahoma Board Game Community's Code of Conduct, and
        the Rust Code of Conduct.
      </p>
      <p class="font-serif-body text-xs text-text-ink-muted mt-1">
        Distributed under a Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike license.
        Suggest edits via <a
          href="mailto:karthikb351@gmail.com"
          class="text-brand-red hover:underline font-bold">email</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
